This paper discusses the challenges and techniques involved in developing an effective Automatic License Plate Recognition (ALPR) system. The paper primarily focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques for localization, segmentation, and recognition of license plates. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for ALPR, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence techniques for ALPR, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the security aspects of ALPR, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of image processing techniques for ALPR, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
